Makes: 1 loafDifficulty: Easy, 1 hour 15 minIngredients:Soft butter, for greasing the panGround almonds180g soft butter180g sugar3 eggsfinely grated zest and juice of 1 orange120g (1 cup) flour60g finely ground almonds10ml (2tsp) baking powder100g orange marmalade20ml orange liqueur 4 marmalades to thrill a new generation of fansMethod1) Heat the oven to 180 C and grease a loaf pan with butter and sprinkle with ground almonds.2) Beat the butter and the sugar in a mixing bowl using an electric whisk. Add the eggs one at a time and combine well. Stir in the orange zest and the juice.3) Mix together the flour, almonds and the baking powder and quickly fold into the wet ingredients. Don't overmix.4) Transfer the mixture to the prepared pan and bake for 35-40 minutes. Test with a wooden skewer to see if it is done. Cool for 5 minutes in the pan before turning out onto a cooling rack and cool completely.5) Place the marmalade and the liqueur in a pot and bring to the boil, stirring continuously. Remove from the heat and brush onto the cake. Leave to dry and then serve sliced.